2. Standard Operating Procedures
Each SOP below covers one complete operation. Follow steps in order. Do not skip steps.


SOP-001  |  Opening the Terminal
Purpose
Open PowerShell in the correct project folder before running any agent
When to use
Before every agent operation
Time required
30 seconds


Steps
Open File Explorer
Navigate to: C:\Projects\FunnyNotFunny\fnf-agents\
Click the address bar at the top of File Explorer
Type: powershell
Press Enter
Confirm the prompt shows: PS C:\Projects\FunnyNotFunny\fnf-agents>

NOTE: Always open PowerShell from the fnf-agents folder. Opening from any other location means your .env file will not load and all API calls will fail.


SOP-002  |  Running the Research Agent
Purpose
Research a topic and save a structured brief to the output/ folder
Prerequisites
Terminal open in fnf-agents folder, Anthropic API key set, Tavily API key set
Output
Markdown research brief saved to output/ folder
Time required
2-5 minutes depending on topic complexity


Steps
Open terminal using SOP-001
Type the command below, replacing the topic with your chosen subject:

python run_agents.py --agent research --topic "your topic here"

Watch the output — you will see [Loop N] Thinking... for each step
When complete you will see [Done] Task complete
Find the output file in C:\Projects\FunnyNotFunny\fnf-agents\output\

Example Commands
Command
Research Topic
python run_agents.py --agent research --topic "wetlands conservation"
Wetland ecosystems
python run_agents.py --agent research --topic "UNDRIP Indigenous rights"
Indigenous sovereignty
python run_agents.py --agent research --topic "factory farming animal welfare"
Animal welfare


NOTE: The agent runs 3-5 web searches automatically. You do not need to do anything while it runs.


SOP-003  |  Running the WordPress Publishing Agent
Purpose
Transform a research brief into a WordPress draft post
Prerequisites
Research brief exists in output/ folder, WordPress Application Password set in .env, permalink structure set to Post Name
Output
Draft post created in WordPress Admin under Posts > All Posts
Time required
1-3 minutes


Steps
Ensure a research brief exists in the output/ folder (run SOP-002 first if needed)
Open terminal using SOP-001
Run the command:

python run_agents.py --agent wordpress

Agent will list files, pick the most recent, format it, and push to WordPress
Note the Post ID from the output — you will need it to publish
Go to funnynfunny.com/wp-admin > Posts > All Posts to review the draft

NOTE: The agent always creates posts as DRAFT. Nothing is published automatically. You must review and publish manually using SOP-004 or SOP-005.


SOP-004  |  Publishing a Draft Post via WordPress Admin
Purpose
Review and publish a draft post from WordPress Admin
When to use
After running SOP-003, when post is ready to go live
Time required
5-10 minutes including review


Steps
Log into funnynfunny.com/wp-admin
Go to Posts > All Posts
Find the draft post — it shows Draft label next to the title
Click the post title to open the editor
Review the content — check headline, brand voice, call to action
Make any edits needed
Click Publish in the top right
Confirm the post is live by visiting the URL

NOTE: Before publishing, confirm: no guilt language, no alarmist framing, ends with an empowering call to action, and correct cause area category is assigned.


SOP-005  |  Publishing a Draft Post via Command Line
Purpose
Publish a draft post directly from PowerShell using the Post ID
Prerequisites
Post exists as Draft in WordPress, Post ID known
Time required
1 minute


Steps
Find your Post ID — run check_posts.py or check the URL in WordPress Admin

python check_posts.py

Run the publish command replacing POST_ID and the title:

python -c "from agent_3_wordpress import WordPressAgent; a = WordPressAgent(); print(a._publish_wp_post(POST_ID, 'Post Title Here'))"

Review the confirmation prompt — verify Post ID and Title are correct
Type YES and press Enter to publish
Copy the URL from the output and verify the post is live

NOTE: Only type YES if you have reviewed the post content. This action publishes immediately. Type anything other than YES to cancel safely.


SOP-006  |  Checking Post Status
Purpose
List all posts and their current status on funnynfunny.com
When to use
When you cannot find a post in WordPress Admin, or need to confirm publish status


Steps
Open terminal using SOP-001
Run:

python check_posts.py

Output shows all posts grouped by status: DRAFT, PUBLISH, PENDING, PRIVATE
Note the ID of any post you need to act on


SOP-007  |  Running the Full Pipeline
Purpose
Run all three agents in sequence — research, content calendar, WordPress
Prerequisites
All three agents configured, Google Sheets credentials set up
Time required
10-15 minutes end to end


Steps
Open terminal using SOP-001
Run the full pipeline with your topic:

python run_agents.py --all --topic "your topic here"

Pipeline runs: Research Agent > Content Calendar Agent > WordPress Agent
Review output folder for research brief
Review Google Sheet for calendar updates
Review WordPress draft and publish when ready using SOP-004 or SOP-005


SOP-008  |  Adding a New API Key
Purpose
Add or update an API key in the .env configuration file
When to use
When adding a new service, rotating a key, or fixing an authentication error


Steps
Open File Explorer and navigate to C:\Projects\FunnyNotFunny\fnf-agents\
Right-click .env > Open with > Notepad
Find the line for the key you want to update
Replace the value after the = sign with your new key
Save the file — Ctrl+S
Close Notepad
Open a fresh PowerShell window and test the relevant agent

NOTE: Never put spaces around the = sign. Never wrap values in quotes. The correct format is: KEY_NAME=value-with-no-quotes

