6. Adding New Agents
The architecture is designed to grow. Every new service — Gmail, Slack, analytics, HR systems — becomes a new agent. Follow this SOP to add one.

SOP-009  |  Adding a New Agent
Steps
Create a new file: agent_4_yourname.py in the fnf-agents folder
Open base_agent.py and read the BaseAgent class — your new agent extends it
Add this template at the top of your new file:

from base_agent import BaseAgentclass MyNewAgent(BaseAgent):    def __init__(self):        super().__init__("My Agent Name")        self.system_prompt = "..."        self.tools = [...]  # define your tools here    def handle_tool_call(self, tool_name, tool_input):        if tool_name == "my_tool":            return self._my_tool(tool_input)        raise ValueError(f"Unknown tool: {tool_name}")

Define your tools — each needs: name, description, input_schema
Implement each tool as a method starting with underscore: _my_tool()
Add the agent to run_agents.py following the existing pattern
Add any new API keys to .env and config.py
Test with a simple goal first before building full functionality

Planned Future Agents
