7. Security Rules
These rules protect your API keys, your website, and your data. Follow them without exception.

Rule
Detail
Never commit .env to GitHub
The .env file contains all your API keys. It is listed in .gitignore. Never remove it from .gitignore.
Never share API keys
Do not paste API keys into chat, email, or documents. Regenerate immediately if a key is exposed.
Use separate keys per purpose
Maintain separate Anthropic keys for: WordPress AI Services, personal Claude, and fnf-agents.
Always use Application Passwords
Never use your WordPress login password for the agent. Always use an Application Password.
Agents never publish without confirmation
The publish function always requires typing YES to confirm. Never modify this behaviour.
Review before publishing
Always read draft posts in WordPress Admin before publishing. Agents make mistakes.


